It's understood that the 48-year-old woman who is believed to be a foreign ambassador was discovered in her office by her driver last night. JOHANNESBURG - Police have confirmed that a senior official at the African Development Bank has been found dead in her office in Centurion.It's understood that the 48-year-old woman, who is believed to be a foreign ambassador, was discovered in her office by her driver on Thursday night.The circumstances surrounding her death are not yet known.The police's Kay Makhubele says authorities have opened an inquest into the death.&quot;We are investigating the circumstances of the death but so far we have opened an inquest case to determine the cause of death. However, our investigation continues.&quot;